Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.39,0:01:38.66,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell’s going on, damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.11,0:01:43.66,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,What’s happening that \NI don’t know about?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.67,0:01:48.12,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Isn’t there...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.12,0:01:50.63,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,anything I can do?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.63,0:01:52.17,B2,GINJO (FLASHBACK),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Here's some advice. {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.17,0:01:54.28,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Act now while you can.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.63,0:01:57.22,B2,GINJO (FLASHBACK),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That's if you want to \Nprotect your family. {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.34,0:02:06.68,B2,VOICE,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You have reached Xcution. {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.68,0:02:09.42,B2,VOICE,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This number is unregistered. {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.42,0:02:12.50,B2,VOICE,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Are you a new member? {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.50,0:02:14.34,B2,VOICE,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Please state your name. {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.34,0:02:16.94,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Ichigo...Kurosaki...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.23,0:02:19.55,B2,VOICE,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Mr. Ichigo Kurosaki?  {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.55,0:02:22.50,B2,VOICE,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We were expecting your call. {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.09,0:02:25.77,B2,VOICE,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Welcome to Xcution. {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.91,0:02:29.61,B2,VOICE (cell phone),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Please redial this number {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.61,0:02:37.89,B2,VOICE (cell phone),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}followed by the digits “00800.” {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.89,0:02:38.66,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.01,0:02:45.96,B2,VOICE (cell phone),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Next, please hang up your phone \Nbefore the second ring tone ends. {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.40,0:02:50.55,B2,VOICE (cell phone),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Your call will be placed \Non your third try. {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.07,0:03:01.60,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,That was a pain in the ass.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.45,0:03:04.03,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Don’t say that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.40,0:03:07.87,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,If I didn’t do that, it’d \Nbe a pain in the ass for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.92,0:03:10.83,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,I need to talk to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.77,0:03:13.01,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,I thought so.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.00,0:03:17.46,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Otherwise, you wouldn’t have called.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.33,0:03:29.26,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,Kurosaki!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.53,0:03:32.94,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,Kurosaki!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.94,0:03:34.65,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,Know anything about Sado?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.06,0:03:38.26,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Your question is too broad.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.83,0:03:39.94,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Know what
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.94,0:03:41.00,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,about him?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.00,0:03:42.14,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,About his condition!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.14,0:03:43.13,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Condition?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.49,0:03:45.49,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Did he catch a cold or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.94,0:03:48.87,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,Oh…
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.87,0:03:50.66,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,Then you don’t know, either?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.30,0:03:54.22,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,I thought I should tell him about \Nwhat happened to Ishida yesterday,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.22,0:03:56.41,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,so I went to his class…
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.41,0:03:59.63,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,Seems Sado hasn’t been \Ncoming to school recently.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.79,0:04:05.78,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,I thought you might know \Nsomething about him, but…
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.25,0:04:10.06,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,I see...so you don’t know, either…
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.40,0:04:15.52,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe I’ll visit Sado at home \Ntoday with a get-well gift…
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.48,0:04:18.40,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,S-Say…
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.40,0:04:21.87,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,Would you like to join me, Kurosaki?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.87,0:04:22.83,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.64,0:04:26.49,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,I have plans today.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.70,0:04:29.10,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,Oh…Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.10,0:04:31.11,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,Of course! This was so sudden!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.11,0:04:35.46,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,All right, I’ll go and let you \Nknow tomorrow how Sado’s doing!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.19,0:04:39.04,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.00,0:04:54.37,B2,ICHIGO (M),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Something happened to Chad, too? {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.36,0:05:02.85,B2,ICHIGO (M),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What the hell is going on?! {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.58,0:05:09.78,B2,GINJO (FLASHBACK),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Today’s too soon. {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.78,0:05:11.57,B2,GINJO (FLASHBACK),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}How about tomorrow? {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.51,0:05:14.00,B2,GINJO (FLASHBACK),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}8 p.m. tomorrow. {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.00,0:05:15.35,B2,GINJO (FLASHBACK),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Come to the front of the {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.35,0:05:17.22,B2,GINJO (FLASHBACK),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}dilapidated apartment \Nbuilding located at 7-1 {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.22,0:05:19.37,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Seventh street in Chobara \NDistrict, Naruki City.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.37,0:05:21.36,B2,GINJO (FLASHBACK),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I’ll hear what you have to say there. {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.56,0:05:27.04,B2,GINJO (FLASHBACK),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Relax. {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.45,0:05:32.50,B2,GINJO (M) (FLASHBACK),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I think I’ll be able to help you. {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.59,0:05:39.19,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,Sado!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.88,0:05:40.85,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.85,0:05:42.74,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,Sado! You there?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.49,0:05:49.19,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe he’s not home?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.09,0:05:51.93,B2,RYUKEN,0000,0000,0000,,If we’re to assume that Uryu was
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.93,0:05:55.00,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,attacked by someone going \Nafter humans like themselves,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.03,0:06:00.00,B2,RYUKEN,0000,0000,0000,,then it means the next one to be \Nin danger is either you, or Sado…
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.19,0:06:02.96,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,No! No! I mustn’t think like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.26,0:06:13.43,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,I pray that Sado will be back at \Nschool tomorrow feeling better!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.43,0:06:19.77,OS,CAPTION,0000,0000,0000,,Here is some tasty bread! \NEnjoy it and get well.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.94,0:06:25.36,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Seventh street…
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.23,0:06:28.36,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,7-1…
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.32,0:06:36.16,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Dilapidated apartments…
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.00,0:06:38.04,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,This must be the place.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.79,0:06:40.57,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.33,0:06:43.35,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Five minutes early…
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.82,0:06:47.61,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Very punctual…
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.85,0:06:52.61,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Not five minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.24,0:06:54.51,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Three.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.59,0:07:00.45,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,So, what did you want to talk about?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.45,0:07:02.24,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,My friends were attacked.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.68,0:07:03.57,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,So?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.01,0:07:05.48,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,I want your help.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.12,0:07:08.99,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,To find who did it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.58,0:07:16.17,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,I thought you don’t trust me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.17,0:07:19.30,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,You know about me and about my dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.30,0:07:21.96,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,You’re no ordinary human.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.63,0:07:24.13,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Think so?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.13,0:07:26.81,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,It’s not that I trust you…
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.73,0:07:30.13,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,But you’re the only guy…
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.13,0:07:34.23,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,You can ask? Is that it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.04,0:07:38.12,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.57,0:07:39.54,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Follow me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.20,0:07:49.02,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Although I wish we could’ve \Ntaken care of my request first.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.63,0:07:56.03,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,You mean about my dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.25,0:07:59.21,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Don’t give me such a scary look.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.20,0:08:06.17,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,There’s no need for you \Nto check on him anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.43,0:08:11.01,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,That was just a pretext \Nto draw your attention.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.49,0:08:12.68,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,A pretext?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.72,0:08:14.81,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,We’re here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.42,0:08:17.45,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Slide the card here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.91,0:08:48.25,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,It’s big…
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.24,0:08:50.86,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,We knocked out five rooms on
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.86,0:08:52.97,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,each side and three \Nstories above and below.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.33,0:08:56.25,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,One of our members is \Na sort of wealthy…
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.92,0:09:00.62,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Now then, before we \Nget to our main topic,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.62,0:09:02.10,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,let me tell you our objective.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.69,0:09:03.89,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Your objective?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.55,0:09:05.51,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah…
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.04,0:09:08.42,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Our objective in approaching you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.34,0:09:15.34,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,It’s to restore your \NSoul Reaper powers.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.49,0:09:21.46,B2,RIRUKA,0000,0000,0000,,God, you’re unbelievable!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.46,0:09:26.04,B2,RIRUKA,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of person sleeps \Nin a place like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.47,0:09:29.89,B2,CHAD,0000,0000,0000,,You’re a grown man! \NWhat are you, stupid?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.89,0:09:31.24,B2,RIRUKA,0000,0000,0000,,For crying out loud!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.24,0:09:34.10,B2,RIRUKA,0000,0000,0000,,You know what it’s like \Nhaving to go look for you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.10,0:09:37.05,B2,RIRUKA,0000,0000,0000,,I never imagined you’d \Nbe in a place like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.67,0:09:41.32,B2,RIRUKA,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, why did he \Nsend me to find you, anyway?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.32,0:09:43.67,B2,RIRUKA,0000,0000,0000,,Ginjo should do it himself!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.67,0:09:44.69,B2,RIRUKA,0000,0000,0000,,Right?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.71,0:09:46.63,B2,RIRUKA,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.63,0:09:48.62,B2,RIRUKA,0000,0000,0000,,Why don’t you say something!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.62,0:09:51.44,B2,RIRUKA,0000,0000,0000,,It’s your fault that \NI’m so upset, you know!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.70,0:09:54.89,B2,RIRUKA,0000,0000,0000,,Come on! You do think, don’t you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.15,0:09:58.24,B2,RIRUKA,0000,0000,0000,,Damn you!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.82,0:10:02.82,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Oww!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.40,0:10:06.43,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,What’s wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.25,0:10:09.60,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,I’m sure you’re not deaf.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.70,0:10:15.62,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Our objective is to restore \Nyour Soul Reaper powers.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.62,0:10:17.38,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,You heard right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.38,0:10:19.90,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,But…how?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.90,0:10:21.93,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,How are you going to restore them?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.42,0:10:24.50,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Why’re you doing this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.13,0:10:26.68,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,For what purpose?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.82,0:10:30.57,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Who the hell are you people?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.08,0:10:35.80,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Calm down.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.80,0:10:37.78,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,I can’t answer your questions
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.78,0:10:39.92,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,if you ask them all at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.60,0:10:45.91,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Sit down.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.23,0:10:47.97,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,The night is long.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.30,0:10:50.77,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,I’ll explain nice and slow.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.54,0:11:00.05,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Want something to drink?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.80,0:11:04.63,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Why’re you looking at me like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.10,0:11:07.55,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn’t serve a minor alcohol.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.07,0:11:09.84,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,You’re not a drinker, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.57,0:11:13.48,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,You seem more straight-laced \Nthan you look.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.85,0:11:15.43,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Anything you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.38,0:11:19.24,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,We don’t have a menu, but \Nwe have pretty much anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.57,0:11:22.66,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,No thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.71,0:11:29.21,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, serve him some orange \Njuice or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.63,0:11:30.62,B2,KUTSUZAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Coming up.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.73,0:11:41.09,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,We’re humans.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.29,0:11:48.29,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, as you say, we are \Nnot “ordinary” humans.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.15,0:11:55.02,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,We’re humans born with \Na certain special ability.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.41,0:11:58.53,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Special ability?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.00,0:12:01.55,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Showing you would be faster.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.47,0:12:37.02,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,What I just did was draw out \Nthe “soul” of the liquor
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.02,0:12:39.71,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,in the glass to “help” me drink it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.74,0:12:42.84,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Our ability is drawing out
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.84,0:12:47.74,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,the “soul” in an object and \Nputting that object to use.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.52,0:12:52.99,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,You have a puzzled look on your face.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.09,0:12:57.93,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Did you think that only \Nliving things had souls?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.96,0:13:02.94,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Each and every object in \Nthis world has a soul,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.84,0:13:05.96,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,not just animals and plants.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.70,0:13:09.20,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,It might be tiny,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.20,0:13:14.24,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,but a telephone pole, a chair, \Neven a glass, possesses a soul.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.68,0:13:19.47,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Ever felt like you can \Nperform much better than
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.47,0:13:22.82,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,usual when using a tool you’re \Ncomfortable working with?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.20,0:13:29.24,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,That shows you understand \Nthat tool’s “soul.”
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.72,0:13:34.46,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,An object’s soul is imbued \Nwith the power to help its user.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.25,0:13:38.20,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,We have the ability to draw that out,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.20,0:13:40.95,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,give it a boost with our own soul,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.95,0:13:43.88,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,and turn it into a greater power.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.53,0:13:46.97,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,I can draw out the soul of asphalt
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.97,0:13:50.93,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,and augment its repulsive \Nforce to jump higher…
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.53,0:13:53.17,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,With a liquid, as you just saw,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.17,0:13:56.35,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,I can make it leap into my mouth
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.75,0:13:59.02,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,or make it support my feet
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.02,0:14:01.33,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,so that I can stand on water.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.34,0:14:06.43,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,And, if it is an object I am \Nfamiliar and compatible with,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.43,0:14:09.73,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,I can even change its form.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.43,0:14:11.70,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,In my case,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.21,0:14:14.02,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,it’s this necklace.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.48,0:14:16.52,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,What’s happening?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.56,0:14:32.33,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Like so.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.50,0:14:40.98,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,We call this ability “Fullbring.”
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.78,0:14:43.55,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Fullbring?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.46,0:14:49.78,B2,RIRUKA,0000,0000,0000,,I’m back!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.27,0:14:52.28,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Riruka.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.97,0:14:55.33,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,You’re back earlier than I expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.33,0:14:56.39,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Did you find him?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.39,0:14:57.80,B2,RIRUKA,0000,0000,0000,,I sure did!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.80,0:15:00.44,B2,RIRUKA,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, that’s your sword glowing \Nover there, isn’t it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.44,0:15:02.58,B2,RIRUKA,0000,0000,0000,,What’s it doing out? Are you stupid?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.84,0:15:04.95,B2,RIRUKA,0000,0000,0000,,God, it’s so dark in here!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.95,0:15:07.05,B2,RIRUKA,0000,0000,0000,,Add more lights right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.05,0:15:09.00,B2,RIRUKA,0000,0000,0000,,I can’t see a thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.00,0:15:11.04,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,I have no plans to add lights.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.04,0:15:12.55,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Put on some glasses…
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.91,0:15:14.87,B2,RIRUKA,0000,0000,0000,,I hate glasses!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.87,0:15:17.06,B2,RIRUKA,0000,0000,0000,,But I hate contacts even more!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.36,0:15:20.73,B2,RIRUKA,0000,0000,0000,,As soon as I put contacts \Nin they make my eyes dry!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.73,0:15:23.50,B2,RIRUKA,0000,0000,0000,,‘Cuz I have big eyes!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.50,0:15:24.78,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Nobody asked...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.62,0:15:26.74,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Who is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.69,0:15:29.53,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Riruka Dokugamine.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.01,0:15:31.07,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,She’s one of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.53,0:15:32.61,B2,RIRUKA,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.61,0:15:34.41,B2,RIRUKA,0000,0000,0000,,Who’s there?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.89,0:15:37.23,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,I’ll introduce you later.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.66,0:15:39.12,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Now hurry up and bring him inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.57,0:15:42.57,B2,RIRUKA,0000,0000,0000,,Don’t boss me around!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.98,0:15:46.54,B2,RIRUKA,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, come on in!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.82,0:15:54.85,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.42,0:15:57.77,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Chad!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.75,0:16:00.03,B2,CHAD,0000,0000,0000,,Ichigo…
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.67,0:16:03.99,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.74,0:16:06.48,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,You haven’t even been \Ncoming to school…
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.82,0:16:08.90,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,So why? What the hell is going on!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.17,0:16:10.19,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,You bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.19,0:16:11.81,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Calm down, Ichigo.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.18,0:16:14.37,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,How can I be calm?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.58,0:16:15.98,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Explain!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.76,0:16:18.20,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Depending on your answer, I…
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.84,0:16:22.22,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Calm down.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.06,0:16:24.96,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Don’t make me say it a third time.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.37,0:16:28.04,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,If you’ll hear me through, \Nyou’ll understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.60,0:16:29.55,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Sit.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.34,0:16:34.35,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,You too, Chad.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.59,0:16:36.52,B2,RIRUKA,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.52,0:16:39.08,B2,RIRUKA,0000,0000,0000,,You guys know each other?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.08,0:16:41.52,B2,RIRUKA,0000,0000,0000,,I wasn’t aware of that!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.77,0:16:44.13,B2,RIRUKA,0000,0000,0000,,Did you know that, Ginjo?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.58,0:16:47.71,B2,RIRUKA,0000,0000,0000,,Don’t tell me I was the \Nonly one kept in the dark?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.09,0:16:51.11,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,A drink for Chad, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.11,0:16:52.49,B2,RIRUKA,0000,0000,0000,,Ignoring me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.73,0:16:53.99,B2,RIRUKA,0000,0000,0000,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.49,0:16:58.40,B2,RIRUKA,0000,0000,0000,,Ichigo? You mean that’s \NIchigo Kurosaki there?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.40,0:17:00.80,B2,RIRUKA,0000,0000,0000,,Turn up the lights! I \Ncan’t see his face!!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.80,0:17:01.50,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Later.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.82,0:17:03.21,B2,RIRUKA,0000,0000,0000,,Why?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.21,0:17:04.54,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Okay…
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.54,0:17:07.00,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Now that everyone’s here, let’s \Nget down to the main topic…
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.00,0:17:09.89,B2,RIRUKA,0000,0000,0000,,All right, now I’m so pissed!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.89,0:17:11.67,B2,RIRUKA,0000,0000,0000,,Show me your face!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.18,0:17:22.96,B2,RIRUKA,0000,0000,0000,,He’s so hot!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.18,0:17:23.93,OS,CAPTION,0000,0000,0000,,He’s so hot!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.06,0:17:31.78,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.11,0:17:33.86,B2,RIRUKA,0000,0000,0000,,I’m…
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.19,0:17:36.64,B2,RIRUKA,0000,0000,0000,,I’m not okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.25,0:17:38.31,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Ignore her.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.76,0:17:41.19,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Ichigo, let’s talk \Nabout our main topic.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.19,0:17:42.58,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, right…
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.86,0:17:45.31,B2,KUTSUZAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Before you do that, Mr. Ginjo,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.82,0:17:48.41,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,would you mind putting the sword away?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.50,0:17:50.71,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Good idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.66,0:18:05.11,B2,KUTSUZAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Be sure to pay for the \Nfloor tiles later.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.11,0:18:06.42,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Good idea…
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.02,0:18:10.42,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Do you understand our power now
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.42,0:18:12.42,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,that you’ve seen it \Nwith your own eyes?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.42,0:18:13.40,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah…
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.79,0:18:14.83,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.35,0:18:17.53,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Now we can move on.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.90,0:18:23.04,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know why a Hollow \Nhas a hole in its chest?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.66,0:18:25.29,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,What’re you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.54,0:18:28.54,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,The pain of not being \Nsaved by a Soul Reaper
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.54,0:18:31.34,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,tears out its heart and leaves a hole…
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.22,0:18:35.26,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,But where does that heart go?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.18,0:18:41.97,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,The lost heart becomes its mask.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.07,0:18:44.72,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Not just its mask.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.72,0:18:48.65,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,A Hollow’s unique appearance \Nand unique powers
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.65,0:18:52.51,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,are all created from the \Nheart that was torn out.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.50,0:18:57.59,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,All of our parents were attacked
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.66,0:19:00.91,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,by Hollows before we were born.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.74,0:19:06.73,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Vestiges of Hollow powers were left
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.73,0:19:09.19,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,behind in the mothers \Nwho were attacked...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.63,0:19:13.29,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,The power inside of us when we were born
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.29,0:19:17.14,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,was more like that of a Hollow \Nrather than of a Soul Reaper.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.08,0:19:21.22,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,We found our power loathsome...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.81,0:19:25.49,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Ichigo, you once possessed \NHollow powers yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.83,0:19:28.50,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,You must understand how we feel.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.49,0:19:44.48,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,We want to rid ourselves \Nof this loathsome power...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.10,0:19:50.06,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Over the course of many years,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.06,0:19:54.17,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,we gradually gathered \Nothers with like powers.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.89,0:19:57.88,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,And that led us to a discovery.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.21,0:20:02.54,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,With our exact opposite...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.00,0:20:07.39,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,That is, someone who possesses \Nboth Soul Reaper and human powers,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.39,0:20:10.68,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,we can exchange powers.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.52,0:20:13.61,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Are you saying...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.18,0:20:15.38,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,There was someone…
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.78,0:20:18.41,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,One other person who, like you,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.05,0:20:22.24,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,was born of a Soul Reaper \Nand a human being.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.11,0:20:27.98,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,By yielding our powers to that person,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.98,0:20:30.39,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,a number of our members in the past
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.39,0:20:32.38,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,were able to return to \Nbeing ordinary humans.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.07,0:20:35.11,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Do you understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.47,0:20:37.50,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,For us to return to \Nbeing ordinary humans,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.97,0:20:41.59,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,it is necessary for you to regain \Nyour Soul Reaper powers...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.18,0:20:51.68,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,That’s not the answer I want to hear.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.09,0:20:53.19,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.41,0:20:59.03,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,I want to know what’s happening \Nto me and my friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.63,0:21:04.07,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Whether I regain my Soul \NReaper powers or not...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.07,0:21:05.58,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,is beside the point.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.67,0:21:18.24,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,So you’re saying you don’t \Nwant your Soul Reaper powers?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.36,0:23:22.92,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Crap, I left something \Nat Ginjo’s place.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.92,0:23:24.01,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,I better call him…
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.56,0:23:26.25,B2,VOICE (CELLPHONE),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You have reached Xcution. {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.25,0:23:27.78,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, hi, I left something at…
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.78,0:23:30.22,B2,VOICE,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Mr. Ichigo Kurosaki? {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.22,0:23:31.24,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I left something…
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.24,0:23:33.12,B2,VOICE,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}“00800.” {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.12,0:23:34.85,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,I have to do this over again?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.85,0:23:37.10,B2,TITLE,0000,0000,0000,,Xcution Dictionary!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.10,0:23:39.23,B2,RIRUKA,0000,0000,0000,,Today, I’ll introduce our members.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.41,0:23:44.63,OS,CAPTION,0000,0000,0000,,Giriko Kutsuzawa
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.86,0:23:41.59,B2,RIRUKA,0000,0000,0000,,Giriko Kutsuzawa!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.59,0:23:44.78,B2,RIRUKA,0000,0000,0000,,He pisses me off sometimes because \NI can’t tell what he’s thinking!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.63,0:23:51.01,OS,CAPTION,0000,0000,0000,,Jackie Tristan
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.27,0:23:47.04,B2,RIRUKA,0000,0000,0000,,Jackie Tristan!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.04,0:23:50.97,B2,RIRUKA,0000,0000,0000,,The way she dresses to flaunt her \Nfigure pisses me off big time!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.01,0:23:55.43,OS,CAPTION,0000,0000,0000,,Yukio
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.56,0:23:52.57,B2,RIRUKA,0000,0000,0000,,Yukio!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.57,0:23:55.60,B2,RIRUKA,0000,0000,0000,,The way this kid talks back \Nat me really pisses me off!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.43,0:23:58.64,OS,CAPTION,0000,0000,0000,,Riruka Dokugamine
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.10,0:23:57.02,B2,RIRUKA,0000,0000,0000,,And...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.02,0:23:58.74,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Riruka Dokugamine...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.74,0:24:02.27,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,A troublesome woman who can’t \Nspeak her honest feelings.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.27,0:24:03.96,B2,RIRUKA,0000,0000,0000,,God, you piss me off!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.96,0:24:05.96,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,